It looks like you added `console.log(salesData)` call inside your `fetchSalesData` function. This won't work because `salesData` doesn't update until `setSalesData` is called. Instead, you can log `salesData` outside of the `fetchSalesData` function, like this:

```
useEffect(() => {
  const fetchSalesData = async () => {
    try {
      const salesCollection = firebase.firestore().collection('Sale');
      const snapshot = await salesCollection.get();
      const data = snapshot.docs.map((doc) => ({ id: doc.id, ...doc.data() }));
      setSalesData(data);
    } catch (error) {
      console.log('Ошибка: ', error);
    }
  };
  fetchSalesData();
}, []);

console.log(salesData);
```

This will log the value of `salesData` after the component has re-rendered, which should contain the data fetched from Firestore.

Note that because `setState` (in this case, `setSalesData`) is asynchronous, you won't be able to log the updated `salesData` immediately after calling `setSalesData`. Instead, you'll need to wait for the component to re-render.

